[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 20 points, counting two extra for the fifth and sixth \Ss. 
Naturally she opens 1\S.

NORTH has a poor hand, but with 7 points he must respond. He has four of partner's \Ss 
so he responds 2\S.

SOUTH KNOWS that 6 + 20 = 26, so she GOES to 4\S.}

